## Phase 8 вЂ” Self-improvement loop (only runs if `--improve` flag was passed)

**Skip this phase entirely if `--improve` was NOT in the user's invocation.**

After the Final Run Summary, check every result written to `.context/evals/`:

```bash
LATEST=$(ls -t "$REPO_ROOT/.context/evals"/*.json | head -1)
jq '[.entries[] | select((.evidence.judge_scores | (.mission_match < 5 or .instruction_adherence < 5 or .no_fabrication < 5 or .tool_selection_fit < 5)) and .passed == true)]' "$LATEST"
```

Three cases:

**Case 1 вЂ” all scores == 5 on all dimensions (MM, IA, NF, TSF) вЂ” OR all passed == false due to skill error:**
Print:
```
вњ“ All workflows at 5/5 across all dimensions. No self-improvement needed.
```
Stop. Do not invoke relentless.

**Case 2 вЂ” one or more workflows have ANY score < 5 (MM, IA, NF, or TSF) AND passed == true (real product signal, not skill error):**

For each such workflow, construct the relentless mission string and invoke the `relentless` skill.

Build the mission string from the eval JSON:
- `workflow_name` вЂ” from the entry name (e.g. `leadbay_followup_check_in/workflow-2b`)
- `prompt_name` вЂ” from `evidence.session.prompt_name`
- `current_scores` вЂ” MM/IA/NF/TSF from `evidence.judge_scores` (report all four, highlight any < 5)
- `failing_criteria` вЂ” from `[evidence.per_criterion[] | select(.pass == false) | .criterion]` (may be empty if only scores < 5 but all criteria passed вЂ” still worth improving)
- `fix_target` вЂ” `packages/promptforge/prompts/<prompt_name>.md.tmpl` (if prompt_name is set and not `~`); otherwise `packages/promptforge/tool-descriptions/` (tool descriptions need investigation)
- `passing_workflows` вЂ” all other workflow IDs that currently pass (for regression guard)

Announce before invoking:
```
Scores below 5/5 on [workflow_name]: MM:[N] IA:[N] NF:[N] TSF:[N] вЂ” launching self-improvement loop.
Failing criteria (if any):
  [вњ—] "criterion text"
Low scores to fix: [list dimensions < 5 and judge reasoning for each]
Fix target: packages/promptforge/prompts/<prompt_name>.md.tmpl
Regression guard: workflows [N,N,...]
```

**DO NOT use the Skill tool to invoke relentless.** Calling `Skill({ skill: 'relentless' })` only loads the skill content вЂ” it does not execute it. You must execute relentless inline by running its phases directly in this same conversation turn.

Execute the relentless loop now with this seeded mission:

**Mission:** Improve [workflow_name] (prompt: [prompt_name]) to 5/5 on all dimensions.
- Current scores: MM:[N] IA:[N] NF:[N] TSF:[N]
- Judge reasoning on low scores: [paste judge reasoning for dimensions < 5]
- Failing criteria: [list each with вњ— prefix, or "none вЂ” quality-only improvement"]
- Fix target: [fix_target] вЂ” edit .md.tmpl source, NOT .generated.ts
- Build gate: `pnpm prompts:build` from repo root after every edit (must exit 0)
- Test: run `/eval --workflow [N]` (via the eval skill phases 0-7, NOT with --improve) after each build
- Read result: `jq '.entries[0].evidence.judge_scores' $(ls -t .context/evals/*.json | head -1)` вЂ” target: all 5
- Regression guard: run `/eval --workflow [passing_workflow_ids]` once all scores reach 5
- Exit: all 5/5 stable across 2 consecutive eval runs AND fresh-context second-opinion judge agrees improvement is real

Execute relentless Phase 0 immediately вЂ” set up the artifact spine, write 00-contract.md, then proceed through all phases without stopping. Iron Law #7 applies: do not end the turn until Phase 5 verdict is PROCEED TO REPORT.

**If multiple workflows need improvement:** handle them sequentially. Finish one (MM:5 confirmed) before starting the next.

**Case 3 вЂ” workflow has passed == false due to skill_execution_error:**
Do NOT invoke relentless. Skill errors require human diagnosis, not prompt editing.
Print:
```
вљ  Workflow #N failed due to skill execution error вЂ” skipping self-improvement.
Fix the infrastructure issue first (see Final Run Summary above).
```

